<L>__{interior dalai lama's private rooms, norbulinka day}
<A>__{in beautiful sunlight, the painted cabinets of this room glisten. rainbows of color play on the glass windows. the dalai lama sits at a low table, a pack of colored pencils, or pastels, spread out around him. he is teaching his little brother to draw. together, little hand in bigger hand, they draw. the dalai lama's mother sits in a side chair, watching her sons. the little boy screams with laughter as the brothers draw a yak.}
